A BILL
To amend sections 2923.123 and 2923.14 of the 1
Revised Code to allow a concealed handgun 2
licensee to carry a handgun in a building or 3
structure that is not a courthouse but in which 4
a courtroom is located in specified 5
circumstances and to permit a nonresident of 6
Ohio to obtain statutory relief from firearms 7
disability based on an Ohio conviction, guilty 8
plea, or delinquent child adjudication. 9
BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF OHIO:
Section 1. That sections 2923.123 and 2923.14 of the 10
Revised Code be amended to read as follows: 11
Sec. 2923.123. (A) No person shall knowingly convey or 12
attempt to convey a deadly weapon or dangerous ordnance into a 13
courthouse or into another building or structure in which a 14
courtroom is located. 15
(B) No person shall knowingly possess or have under the 16
person's control a deadly weapon or dangerous ordnance in a 17
courthouse or in another building or structure in which a 18
courtroom is located. 19

